<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Credit2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Credit,</orth> vb. 1) to believe: <bibl n="shak. son 138.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 138, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.245" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 245</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.120" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 124</bibl>.<lb />2) to do honour: <cit><quote>I call them forth to c. her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 106</bibl></cit> (misunderstood by Grumio who replies: <emph>Why, she comes to borrow nothing of them</emph>).
